lyrics:
10 contributorswas it 26 lyricsverse 1
livin hard was easy when i was young and bulletproof
i had no chains to bind me just a guitar and a roof
emptied every bottle when i poured i never missed
i had blood shot eyes at twentyfive or was it twentysix

verse 2
didnt seem to matter what price i had to pay
cause anything worth havin i’d just lose anyway
friends worried about me they’d asked if i was sick
thought i wouldn’t die at twentyfive or was it twentysix

chorus
those two years run together like whiskey over ice
meltin into memories like somebody elses life
i’m glad to say i’ve come around
but if i could have one wish
i’d like another try at twentyfive
or was it twentysix

verse 3
